{
  "stem": "10572.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You know, nobody told you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You didn't get an itinerary.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the sun was rising over the city.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That was well known to us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we somehow felt maybe we never see the city again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And a friend of my father-- and I don't know how he got it in-- had a book, that he carried in-- with him.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And my father tore the cover page out of the and converted it into a postcard and wrote a postcard to my mother-- and lied that we were fine, and that we had confidence, and we wanted them to be brave and have faith.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And one of the men in our [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] compartment in the train was our doctor, Dr.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Cohen, Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Leopold Cohen, who had lost his left leg during the First World War as a surgeon on the front and was known in Hildersheim always with a black cane in order to-- and he was on our train.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were greeted by SS-- young SS with fixed bayonets and clubs, and were driven from the train into the underpass of the Weimar station.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, and as long as I live, I will never forget the white tiles of the underpass there, facing the white tiles and surrounded by the threatening SS who beat up on us.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a man standing next to me, a lawyer from Hanover, Egon Berkowitz, who had, as an officer during the First World War-- was wounded so badly that he got the golden-- wounded-- And he had a silver plate on his head.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he passed out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He said, we know your war wounds.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He said, this animal will get up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Or he will stay there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Well, Egon Berkowitz survived, and survived the war.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He got out.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we got-- we were loaded-- ultimately were loaded on buses on our way to Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And as we were-- arrived at the Grosse Tor, the main gate to Buchenwald-- which had this ridiculous sign on it, 'Right or Wrong, My Country'-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] we got off.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were driven through the main gate.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And in front of us were SS, who kicked us in our shins and drove us back.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there were others who pushed us from behind.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And those of us who were young enough, who could run fast enough, survived.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And many of us got killed right then and there, with broken bones, were lying on the grounds of the November night in Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there were, that night, 11,000 prisoners brought to Buchenwald the same way we arrived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there were-- we were put into barracks.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were still hammering this very primitive wooden structure, built on the clay ground of Buchenwald, without heat, without light, without facilities, without toilets, without water.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I had found my father again.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had him in front of me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I begged my father to close his eyes and close his ears and not hear and see what we saw there for the simple reason that we had to stay sane.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we saw during those first three days [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] many, many people jumping against the electric voltage barbed wire to commit suicide.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We, we were housed in these wooden-- on wooden floors and four stories high.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and there was no water.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were-- some of us, I think, went out of their mind because of thirst.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And this all was surrounded by this-- the whole camp was surrounded by electric voltage barbed wire.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they had the tower guards with their guns threatening us with the, [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] the big, big lights that were constantly rotating.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was a ghostly-- it was on a-- we were on a planet that was beyond any description and any-- And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I, I thought that day and the next day-- I said, if any one of us escape here to tell the world--",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We, [PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] we had five barracks, the Juden Baraken, the 'Jew barracks.' And the 11,000 were put in those five barracks.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were like herrings, or sardines, next to each other, those four stories.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Pictures of them-- pictures that are known today, were shown in And the unbelievable thing was that the first couple of days we're not doing anything.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were standing outside the barracks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was raining.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And some people were-- had used their hats to catch the rain, hoping that they would catch enough rain to wet their tongues.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And during those first three nights-- three days-- we saw many-- and some of our friends-- lose their mind and go berserk.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
